This paper deals with processing stream data, which is a common topic in the database community (cs.DB). The problem of missing or incomplete data attributes is also a key focus of the paper, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed approach involves imputing missing attributes using differential dependency rules, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also discusses strategies for reducing the search space, which is relevant to the field of cryptography (cs.CR).
